<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 9:01AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Light to occasionally moderate snowfall will continue to impact
the Tri-Cities as a snowband tracks northeast across the area.
* Intervals of snowfall rates up to an inch per hour will be
possible within this snowband.
* Temperatures at or below 32F combined with higher intensity
snowfall rates will allow snow to accumulate on roadways.
IMPACTS...
* Reductions in visibility under one mile will be possible at
times.
* Slippery conditions will continue through mid-morning. Drivers
should be prepared for variable road conditions and allow
extra time while traveling.
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
